<item>
            <title>[LU-16577] Provide vvp_set_folio_dirty_batched() and wrappers for page users</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16577</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16433&quot; title=&quot;single client performance regression in SSF workload &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-16433&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-16433&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; there is discussion about if and how we can recapture the lost performance from being unable to use Patrick&apos;s vvp_set_pagevec_dirty() since losing access to account_page_dirtied().&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is an attempt to provide a replacement in vvp_folio_account_dirtied() with the caveat that some memcg and writeback ratelimit calculations will be wrong:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;here:&lt;br/&gt;
-&lt;del&gt;&amp;gt; __this_cpu_add(bdp_ratelimits, nr); &amp;lt;&lt;/del&gt;- no access&lt;br/&gt;
and here:&lt;br/&gt;
-&lt;del&gt;&amp;gt; mem_cgroup_track_foreign_dirty(folio, wb); &amp;lt;&lt;/del&gt;- no access&lt;/p&gt;

</description>
